The questions and answers
=========================

0:   Why does my system freeze after installing emx 0.9c or later?

  You are probably using a version of Siegfried Hanisch's ScreenSaver
  which breaks with emx 0.9c and later.  Please upgrade to version 2.6
  of ScreenSaver.

1:   How can I create an application which doesn't need emx.dll?

  Compile and link with the -Zomf and -Zsys options of GCC.  Example:

      gcc -Zomf -Zsys myprog.c

  Note that fork() and some other features are not available when
  using the -Zomf and -Zsys options.

2:   Compiling and linking with the -Zomf option fails; LINK386
     complains about not finding libraries c_alias.lib, gcc.lib,
     c.lib, etc.:

       LINK386 :  warning L4051: c_alias.lib : cannot find library

     Compiling and linking without the -Zomf option works.

  You forgot to run `omflibs' in the \emx\lib directory after
  unpacking the ZIP files.

